HEADWORD: Carbunculation
<hw>Car*bun`cu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>carbunculatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The blasting of the young buds of
trees or plants, by excessive heat or cold.</def>
